  "texts": [
    "By Lemma 2.1, we have|⟨dπ 1 ∧ • • • ∧ dπ k, v 1 ∧ • • • ∧ v k ⟩| ≤ k j=1 Lip(π j) for v 1,..., v k ∈ R d of norm at most 1.",
    "(2.3)We will convene to usually omit the differential dL d when integrating with respect to the Lebesgue measure.",
    "Thus, we write, for example,E f det Dπ = E f det Dπ dL d.The following lemma is a well known property of determinants, which may be found e.g.",
    "in the book of Ambrosio at al [3,Theorem 2.16], see also Lang [30,Proposition 2.6].",
    "Lemma 2.7 (Joint continuity of determinants)."
  ]
}